Package insect.coverage.execution

Class Summary
Bag Bag.java Provides a collection to keep track of the number of each particular item added.
BlockMonitor Provides methods for instrumented programs to report coverage of basic block at runtime.
BranchMonitor Provides methods for instrumented programs to report values evaluated in conditional branches during runtime.
CallMonitor Provides methods for instrumented programs to report the invocation of methods during runtime.
CatchMonitor Provides methods for instrumented programs to report exceptions caught during runtime.
ExecClassLoader Extends the functionality of URLClassLoader to allow a class not located in the JVM classpath to be loaded, even if a class of that name has already been loaded by the bootstrap classloader.
ExecThread Thread to perform execution of another program.
ExecThreadGroup Thread group for the ExecThread so that exceptions from multi-threaded and Swing/AWT applications can be caught.
ExecutionSecurityManager Security manager to prevent executing programs from exited the virtual machine.
Executor Executes an instrumented program with the given arguments within a single instance of the VM.
InitMonitor InitMonitor.java Ensures that all InsECT variables are properly set for the initialization of the rest of the monitors.
ThrowMonitor Provides methods for an instrumented program to report exceptions thrown during runtime.
VarStack VarStack.java Serves as a "secondary" stack for the instrumentation probes to use during execution.
